158 “The office shall immediately send any notification or report of a death under the
159 circumstances enumerated in clause (15) to the state child fatality review team established by
160 section 15 of chapter 18C, including, but not limited to, the known facts concerning the time,
161 place, manner, circumstances and cause of such death. The chief medical examiner shall provide
162 any additional information related to such notification or report to the state child fatality review
163 team upon request.”
